we can multiply both the numerator and denominator by the square root of 3 to get rid of the radical sign: \begin{align*}
\frac{5}{\sqrt{3}} &= \frac{5}{\sqrt{3}\sqrt{3}} = \frac{5\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{3}} = \frac{5\sqrt{3}}{3} = \boxed{\frac{5\sqrt{3}}{3}}
\end{align*}
